flowRoot.flowPara: The Rifton allows Jerome to walk. The arm wraps help him bear weight. He needs to use his 2 shoes while walking, not only one because of hip displacement. Do not feed him while he is in the walker or stander, he can choke if doesnt have good posture.
The wooden chair allows Jerome to sit and eat. His feet are flat on his footrest and his knees are bent. His bum is right back in the chair.
A tray helps him support his trunk with his hands.
